    "crt:geographicScope": "UK primary, EU secondary",
    "crt:notes": "Antiques domain instance v1.0.0. Nineteen role archetypes spanning the full antiques trade ecosystem. B2B roles cover the professional and institutional buyer/seller market (auction directors, valuers, estate executors, trade dealers, insurance underwriters, museum curators, private equity collectors, art advisors, probate solicitors, logistics specialists). B2C roles cover the private buyer spectrum from expert Serious Collector to casual Home Decorator, including Inheritor and Gift Buyer as event-triggered archetypes and Young Collector as an emerging digital-first segment. B2B2C roles (Interior Designer, Retail Dealer) sit at channel boundaries. Section 6 qualification examples provide full worked evaluations for three archetypal edge-case or illustrative scenarios."
